 estimate of the neutrino cross sections. In addition, the analysis\nof the $(e,e^\\prime p)$ data will help a number of theoretical developments,\nlike the description of final-state interactions needed to isolate the\ninitial-state contributions to the observed single-particle peaks, that is also\nneeded for the interpretation of the signal detected in neutrino experiments.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 16 Jun 2014 17:39:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-06-17"}
