{"id":"1406.4133","submitter":"Maria J. Rodriguez","authors":"Alexandru Lupsasca, Maria J. Rodriguez and Andrew Strominger","title":"Force-Free Electrodynamics around Extreme Kerr Black Holes","comments":"24 pages. v2: minor edits, matches published version. Related videos\n  available at\n  http://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLsrfyTK-g7cP-_8F7A5Zb71K_94_gaXgn","journal-ref":"JHEP 1412 (2014) 185","doi":"10.1007/JHEP12(2014)185","report-no":null,"categories":"hep-th astro-ph.HE gr-qc","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Plasma-filled magnetospheres can extract energy from a spinning black hole\nand provide the power source for a variety of observed astrophysical phenomena.\nThese magnetospheres are described by the highly nonlinear equations of\nforce-free electrodynamics, or FFE. Typically these equations can only be\nsolved numerically. In this paper we consider the FFE equations very near the\nhorizon of a maximally spinning black hole, where the energy extraction takes\nplace. Thanks to an enhanced conformal symmetry which appears in this\nnear-horizon region, we are able to analytically obtain several infinite\nfamilies of exact solutions of the full nonlinear equations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 16 Jun 2014 20:00:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 19 Mar 2015 19:55:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-03-20"}
