alization rate to the dissipation rate was a dependent of the\nmolecular species, and especially faster solvent thermalization rate of\n9-(6-(azulen-1-yl)hexyl)anthracene was predicted. The vibrational\ncharacteristics of this solvent are discussed in the relation to the\nvibrational modes and structures of the bridged compounds.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 16 Jun 2014 20:37:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-06-18"}
